    "text": "Recovery Startup Assistance Act\n\nThis bill expands the employee retention tax credit to include recovery startup businesses. The bill defines recovery startup business as any employer that began a trade or business after February 15, 2020, had less than 50 full-time employees, and did not have gross receipts in excess of $25,000 in the preceding five-year period."
